  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. An uncertainty quantification campaign was conducted covering material property variability, geometric tolerances, and boundary condition sensitivity; results informed the acceptance bounds and are summarised in the validation report (see hasValidationResult). The UQ campaign demonstrated that predicted QoIs are most sensitive to cortical bone modulus and rod pre-bend angle, both of which were directly measured for each specimen. Aggregate E/uval < 1.96 for all three QoIs across both laboratories.",
